<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,151,364]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,263,289]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[620,736,264,290]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavida">
<emphasis box="[620,641,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[655,736,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">flavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it in having broad gena which is more than 1/2 eye height, distinct black inner vittae on postsutural scutum, more broad pruinosity on abdominal tergites, and dense yellowish white pruinosity on anterior 1/2 of tergite 5. We have not seen a male of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
